Package: cryptkey-rpifwcrypto
Architecture: arm64
Maintainer: Tom Dewey <tom.dewey@raspberrypi.com>
Depends: busybox | coreutils, rpifwcrypto, block-device-id
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Description: Device-bound cryptographic key via firmware HMAC
 Generates a device-bound cryptographic key by computing an HMAC of the
 block device's unique identifier (CID for MMC/SD, EUI for NVMe, or
 serial) using the Raspberry Pi firmware crypto hardware key slot. Used
 by cryptroot as the primary key source. Requires rpifwcrypto and
 block-device-id packages. USB devices are not supported.
